{"index": 507, "title": "DevOps Engineer", "job_location": "Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland", "jd_text": "At eBay, we're more than a global ecommerce leader \u2014 we\u2019re changing the way the world shops and sells. Our platform empowers millions of buyers and sellers in more than 190 markets around the world. We\u2019re committed to pushing boundaries and leaving our mark as we reinvent the future of ecommerce for enthusiasts.Our customers are our compass, authenticity thrives, bold ideas are welcome, and everyone can bring their unique selves to work \u2014 every day. We're in this together, sustaining the future of our customers, our company, and our planet.Join a team of passionate thinkers, innovators, and dreamers \u2014 and help us connect people and build communities to create economic opportunity for all.About The Team And The RoleNative Platform Engineering owns the end-to-end systems that build, test, sign, and release eBay\u2019s global iOS and Android applications. Our Mobile DevOps team operates a distributed CI/CD platform composed of high-throughput Jenkins and GitHub Actions pipelines, large-scale macOS/Xcode and Android build fleets, hybrid cloud and on-prem compute, and production-grade observability systems.We approach this as a systems engineering problem: throughput, determinism, isolation, fault domains, capacity modeling, and secure supply chain design all matter. As a DevOps Engineer (SE3), you will contribute to the reliability and evolution of this shared platform, improving subsystems while ensuring they integrate cleanly into the broader architecture. You\u2019ll work closely with peers across platform, infrastructure, security, and mobile engineering to strengthen the whole system rather than operate in isolation. This role reports to the DevOps Engineering Manager and is based on-site in Dublin.We value engineers who think in terms of systems, constraints, and trade-offs. If you are motivated by improving complex engineering platforms that enable teams to ship reliably at global scale, we encourage you to apply.What you will accomplishImprove system throughput and determinism across CI/CD pipelines by reducing flakiness, optimizing parallelization, and improving cache efficiency and stage isolation.Increase fleet reliability and performance through capacity planning, autoscaling strategies, workload scheduling, and failure-domain analysis across macOS and Android runners.Strengthen observability across subsystems by instrumenting metrics and logs, building actionable dashboards, and improving time-to-detection and time-to-recovery.Enhance software supply chain integrity by advancing secure code signing, secrets management, artifact validation, and automated security controls within CI workflows.Contribute to operational excellence by participating in incident response, performing root cause analysis, and implementing systemic reliability improvements.Collaborate across engineering domains to evolve platform architecture, share knowledge, and continuously improve developer productivity at scale.What you will bringExperience engineering or operating production CI/CD systems (e.g., Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI) with an understanding of pipeline architecture and failure modes.Strong systems-level diagnostic skills in Linux and macOS environments, including command-line diagnostics and performance analysis.Proficiency in automation and scripting (e.g., Python, Bash) and familiarity with infrastructure automation concepts.Working knowledge of distributed systems fundamentals, including networking (TCP/IP, DNS, load balancing), resource isolation, and secure system design.Experience with cloud infrastructure (Azure, GCP, or equivalent) and an understanding of scalability and fault tolerance principles.Ability to work on-site in Dublin, collaborate across time zones, and participate in business-hours operational support.Additional DetailseBay is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, and disability, or other legally protected status. If you have a need that requires accommodation, please contact us at talent@ebay.com. We will make every effort to respond to your request for accommodation as soon as possible. View our accessibility statement to learn more about eBay's commitment to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities.We use cookies to enhance your experience and may use AI tools for administrative tasks in the hiring process. To learn how we handle your personal data and use AI responsibly, please visit our Talent Privacy Notice, Privacy Center, and AI Hiring Guidelines.\n\nBegin your response with {\n", "v15_labels": {"loc_raw": "Dublin, County Dublin, Ireland", "loc": "OUTSIDE_UK", "arr_raw": "based on-site in Dublin", "arr": "IN_OFFICE", "sen_raw": "DevOps Engineer (SE3)", "sen": "LEVEL_3", "tech_raw": "Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Python, Bash, Azure, GCP", "tech": ["OOS"], "comp_raw": null, "comp": "NO_GBP"}}
