{"index": 537, "title": "Manager - Software Engineer", "job_location": "Australia", "jd_text": "Job DescriptionKPMG\u2019s Deal Advisory and Infrastructure Technology & Innovation team are a small but rapidly growing team within KPMG\u2019s Deal Advisory and Infrastructure practice, which comprises over 1,400 professionals across ASPAC (including more than 1,000 in Australia). Our mission is to design and deliver cutting-edge technology, data, and AI solutions that support both ASPAC and global initiatives.With a start-up mentality and the freedom to innovate, we combine deep deal and infrastructure expertise with advanced analytics, automation, and emerging technologies to create impactful solutions for our clients. If you\u2019re passionate about building transformative tools and shaping the future of deal technology, this is your opportunity to join a team that values creativity, agility, and collaboration. Your OpportunityAs a Software Engineer, you will join a small growing team of technology and innovation professionals and will drive the technology decisions to enable KPMG to put best of breed products in the market. This will involve designing and stewarding new solutions for the Deal Advisory & Infrastructure division of the firm from feasibility through to deployment and its ongoing operations.The role includes:Working on complex solution architecture projects from conception to implementation, consulting with stakeholders to capture requirements and translating them into viable solutions along with project sizing and estimation.Design, implement, and roll out cutting-edge software, AI, and analytics solutions that drive innovation and deliver measurable impact for clients and stakeholders. You will work at the forefront of technology, collaborating with cross-functional teams to architect and deploy scalable, high-performance systems that solve complex business challenges and enable data-driven decision-making.Work with a team of developers to deliver inn